cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about using convolutional neural networks for image reconstruction in X-ray computed tomography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential for generalization to a wide range of applications, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
